parameters: \n<Innkeeper>Welcome to the inn, traveler! What will it be toda-\..\..\..\|\^
\elleIt's been a long time, hasn't it, \|Darius?
\elleOf course it's me! Why do you look like you've seen a ghost?
\n<Darius>I'm just happy to see you! Have you been well staying in Gerth?
\lyonIt is true. We've just come from there. I've seen firsthand the destruction of the town.
\elleLyon saved me when the attack happened. I owe him both my life and his right to privacy.
\n<Darius>I see. We all have our reasons to keep secrets.
\n<Darius>But if you had the heart to save dear Elle, I know that you are one I can trust.
\elleHe really is nicer than he looks.
\elleWhat do you think I mean when you put up a face like that?
\n<Darius>Say... what now? With Gerth gone, what brings you two here? Asylum, perhaps?
\elleWhile that would be nice, we were heading west to Rivelt. We wanted to see if they knew anything about the bandits.
\n<Darius>Rivelt... I would ask you a favour in that case.
\n<Darius>It's Albien\..\..\.. I sent him off on an errand to Rivelt a few days ago and he hasn't returned still.
\n<Darius>Yes, Albien, my beloved son. I fear for the worst. I have word that a few warriors from the capital were arriving here soon.
\n<Darius>I'm quite worried. There has been no word from Rivelt in over a week now. I thought it suspect, and now more so with the disappearance of my boy.
\elleWe will find him. Albien is near and dear to me.
\lyonIs that so? \|Well, since we are heading there already, I guess I see no problem.
\n<Darius>If you learn anything, please let me know. As soon as the warriors from the capital arrive I will be sending them after you as well.
\n<Darius>And feel free to rest or purchase some items from the stalls outside.
\lyonThat may be in our best interest, especially for the long journey ahead.
\elleLet's not waste too much time! Albien may need us!
\n<Darius>Welcome back, friends! Care to stay and rest a while? 50 Coin.
\n<Darius>You can't afford it, huh? No matter, just this once you may stay on the house. But only this time. I need to keep the lights on.
\n<Darius>Hope to see you again soon! Bring Coin next time!
\n<Darius>I'm afraid I can't do the same favour as last time. Come back when you have the Coin.
\n<Darius>Fair enough. My doors are always open.
\n<Hungry Man>Ah! I've been looking forward to this breakfast all morning!
\n<Hungry Man>Do you mind? \| It is awfully hard to eat with you staring like that.
\n<Reading Man>I see\..\..\.. To think that attacking a scorched enemy with ice would be so devastating. Could the opposite be true for chilled enemies?
\n<Reading Man>Hmm\..\..\.. I did not know a family once lived up there by the shore.  What happened to them, I wonder.
\n<Reading Man>Sound, as a weapon?... That, I'd like to see.\| Or should I say "hear"?
\n<Reading Man>This book\..\..\.. goes on a lot of tangents.
\n<Pianist>I do hope you are enjoying this music.
